wing in public locations such as a mall? <br>   Thanks in advance for any help. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/udreadedfist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DreadedFist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/26/02 10:31:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4044.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Life/Gesture Drawing in Malls and Other Public Locations</span><hr size=1> I guess if the people are not gonna spend alot of time in one pose, then draw people sitting down or standing/chilling.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ufluxhavoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FluxHavoc</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://server2039.virtualave.net/xenoflare/misc/glowball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Artist in Residence</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/26/02 3:36:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4044.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://server2039.virtualave.net/xenoflare/misc/thumb60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Life/Gesture Drawing in Malls and Other Public Locations</span><hr size=1> Yeah. You would have, say, 3-4 sketches per page. Use ink or felt tip only, and try to express the entire gesture of people with only several lines.<br><br>One of the things to watch out for is the relationship of the figure to the environment. Chairs, tables, counters, etc etc. Don't worry TOO much about clothing, but sometimes the clothing can play a big part in balance.<br><br>Another thing to watch out for is.... that you can't express EVERYTHING. You have to choose which lines to skip and let the viewer fill in the gaps. Kinda like those Metal Gear Solid 2 sketches you know?<br><br>Most sketches would be 5 to 10 second drawings anyways. Twenty seconds if you're lucky. If you find people sitting in dining places eating and stuff they go back to their position many times and you'll have many chances to add detail to your sketch if you wish.<br><br>Anyways I hope that helps. Good luck and have fun!! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p><embed src="http://xenoflare.virtualave.net/misc/fluxsig2002.swf" width="170" height="60"></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ufluxhavoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FluxHavoc</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://server2039.virtualave.net/xenoflare/misc/glowball.gif" BORDER=0> at: 7/26/02 3:38:19 pm<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=4044.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showNextMessage?topicID=4044.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4044.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.emailToFriend?topicID=4044.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.threadControl?topicID=4044.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Top